verbose_text: RANKL, a member of the tumor necrosis factor (TNF) superfamily, interacts with receptor activator of nuclear factor-kappaB (RANK) that is expressed on OC progenitors, and then binds to TNF receptor associated factor 6 (TRAF6) to activate downstream signaling cascades, such as the mitogen activated protein kinase (MAPK)/nuclear factor-kappaB (NF-kappaB) signal pathway, to promote OC formation and bone resorption.
